This paper discusses the impact of website design on user navigation, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of topological measures to assess the impact of changes on user navigation, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of click biases and link insertion, which could be related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
